BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 New Section; New Hampshire-Greece Trade Council. Amend RSA 12-O by inserting after
2 section23-athefollowingnewsection:
3 12-O:23-b NewHampshire-GreeceTradeCouncil.
4 I. Thegeneralcourtfindsasfollows:
5 (a) Greek-AmericanswereanimportantpartofNewHampshire'searlyhistory.
6 (b) GreeceisoneofNewHampshire’slargesttradepartners.
7 (c) New Hampshire should build upon its historic, cultural, and economic ties with the
8 RepublicofGreece.
9 (d) New Hampshire has the highest per capita concentration of Greek Americans in the
10 country.
11 II. The commissioner of the department of business and economic affairs and the secretary
12 of state shall have the authority to establish a New Hampshire-Greece trade council to meet with
13 oneormoretradecouncilsestablishedbytheRepublicofGreece. Thepurposeofthecouncilshallbe
14 to advance bilateral trade and investment between New Hampshire and Greece, initiate joint action
15 on policy issues of mutual interest to New Hampshire and Greece, and promote business and
16 academicexchangesbetweenNewHampshireandGreece.
17 III. Themembersofthecouncilshallinclude:
18 (a) Twosenators,appointedbythepresidentofthesenate.
19 (b) Twohousemembers,appointedbythespeakerofthehouseofrepresentatives.
20 (c) The commissioner of the department of business and economic development, or their
21 designee.
22 (d) Thesecretaryofstate,ortheirdesignee.
23 (e) A representative from the business and industry association, appointed by that
24 organization.
25 (f) A representative of the division of economic development, appointed by the
26 commissionerofthedepartmentofbusinessandeconomicaffairs.
27 (g) A representative of the university system of New Hampshire, appointed by the
28 chancellor.
29 (h) Twopublicmembers,appointedbythegovernor.
30 IV. Thecouncilshallelectachairperson,whosedutiesshallincludecallingmeetings.

